{"name":"Armor Training (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[zD0XifvCmxfSzn1Y]{Guard}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You reduce the armor check penalty of armor you wear by 1 (to a minimum of 0) and increase the maximum Dexterity bonus allowed by your armor by 1.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Guard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"0BuUApK6X23K4pvB"}
{"name":"Explosives Acumen (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">@Item[FkuDc522TWw3WGHE]{Bombard}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You increase the DC to avoid attacks you make using weapons with the explode special property by 1. You reduce the amount of any damage you take from any weapon with the explode special property by an amount equal to your Strength bonus.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Bombard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"4th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"284OAjjb72jiK0J7"}
{"name":"Secondary Style Technique","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;<a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-entity=\"Item\" data-id=\"WXbhhtFOi9TdKT0y\"> Soldier</a></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">At 9th level and every 4 levels thereafter, you gain a style technique unique to your secondary fighting style. For the purposes of these style techniques, treat your soldier level as equal to your soldier level &ndash; 8.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"9th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"2Cn70odJvnnXFxas"}
{"name":"Elusive Target (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[FoZjqRj66PMeoSLh]{Hit-and-Run}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">On any turn in which you move, you gain a +1 insight bonus to your AC until the start of your next turn.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Hit-and-Run","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"4th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"2UL8gY5g49yU5n9t"}
{"name":"Electric Arc (Ex; 7th Level)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl09_LabelName\">When you hit a target with a weapon in the shock category, electricity arcs out from your original target to deal electricity damage to a secondary subject within 10 feet of the original target. This damage is equal to the weaponâ€™s level. The secondary subject must be the creature nearest to the original target (your choice if multiple creatures are equidistant).<br><br>This gear boost does not function for weapons that have the explode or blast special property. If you use this gear boost with a weapon with the arc critical hit effect (see page 182), your secondary subject for electric arc must be the same as your secondary subject for the arc critical effect.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"7th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"33vaOvpOdmeKyCvl"}
{"name":"Power of Legend (Su; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[33fxlqpShtqndjry]{Arcane Assailant}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You can call on the link between you and the legendary heroes who wielded powerful magic weapons eons ago to overcome adversity. As a move action when wielding a magic weapon or a weapon imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to end one of the following conditions affecting you: bleeding, burning, confused, exhausted, fatigued, flat-footed, off-target, shaken, or sickened. Alternatively, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to change the cowering condition to the frightened condition or change the frightened condition to the shaken condition. In this case, the new condition lasts for the same duration the original condition would have and can&rsquo;t be further affected by this ability.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Arcane Assailant","type":"","activation":{"type":"move","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"3d0DEjSFpCRYDdjn"}
{"name":"Arcane Attack (Su; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[33fxlqpShtqndjry]{Arcane Assailant}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to use a weapon imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight to make an attack that strikes true. This attack ignores all cover and concealment, including total concealment (though you must at least be aware of a creature&rsquo;s presence to target it with this attack). If the attack is a ranged attack, the target must be within the first range increment. The attack only affects your selected target, even if it normally affects an area or multiple targets. You still must make a normal attack roll, and if your attack misses, it has no effect.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Arcane Assailant","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"4MYt0ywJeqH8AAPj"}
{"name":"Sonic Resonance (Ex; 7th Level)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl03_LabelName\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl20_LabelName\">When you hit a creature within 30 feet of you using a weapon in the sonic category, the sonic energy continues to resonate within that creature, giving it the flat-footed condition for 1 round. If you hit multiple creatures at the same time (such as with an automatic, blast, or explode weapon), only the creature nearest to you or to the center of the explosion (your choice if multiple creatures are equidistant) is affected.</span><br></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"7th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"4QvOqn2DiIptlpwi"}
{"name":"On the Bounce (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[ZST4GXqgA9b9CzNU]{Armor Storm}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You learn to control your armor with such ease, you are actually more maneuverable in it than out of it. While wearing heavy armor or powered armor, you can move up to your speed when you make a full attack. You can move before or after all your attacks, but not both. If you have the Shot on the Run feat, you can divide your movement to move both before and after making a full attack as long as all the attacks are ranged attacks. If you have the Spring Attack feat, you can divide your movement to move both before and after making a full attack as long as all the attacks are melee attacks. If you have both feats, your attacks can be any combination of melee and ranged attacks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Armor Storm","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"6Ofm6Ak0JcXCgugV"}
{"name":"Bullet Barrage (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl04_LabelName\">You gain a +1 insight bonus to damage rolls for weapons in the projectile category. This bonus increases by 1 for every 4 soldier levels you have.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"6QrphfAbQgZZlRan"}
{"name":"Mobile Army (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[ZST4GXqgA9b9CzNU]{Armor Storm}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You become a master of all weapons associated with your armor. You deal 1d6 additional damage with any attack from a weapon that is part of your armor, including unarmed attacks using the hammer fist ability and weapons that have been attached to your armor as an armor upgrade. The additional damage is of the same type as the weapon&rsquo;s normal type. Also, while wearing heavy or powered armor, you gain a +2 bonus to your KAC against combat maneuvers.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Armor Storm","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"4th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"7NCQCsW6RZBdRODP"}
{"name":"Impactful Attack (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">@Item[FkuDc522TWw3WGHE]{Bombard}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a full action, you can make a ranged attack that knocks enemies back. Targets you hit are knocked back 5 feet from you. If you use a weapon with the explode special property, all targets that fail their saving throws are instead knocked back 5 feet from the center of the explosion. An enemy that you critically hit or that rolls a natural 1 on its saving throw is also knocked prone. You canâ€™t make an impactful attack with an automatic weapon, but you can use this ability with a weapon that has the blast special property.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Bombard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"7jysdYZJiChYwqdu"}
{"name":"Heavy Fire (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">@Item[FkuDc522TWw3WGHE]{Bombard}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You can use your physical power to steady your weapon and make your attacks more dangerous. As a full action, you can make a single ranged attack that deals additional damage equal to your Strength bonus to all targets. You can use this ability in conjunction with the automatic, explode, or unwieldy special property (see pages 180â€“182).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Bombard","type":"","activation":{"type":"full","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"9FUOazsyfTOKikav"}
{"name":"Impenetrable Defense (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[zD0XifvCmxfSzn1Y]{Guard}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can set up a strong defense for yourself and an adjacent ally. Until the start of your next turn, you gain three benefits: your damage reduction increases to DR 10/â€”; you and the chosen ally each gain a +4 bonus to AC; and if you use guardâ€™s protection, you direct all the damage to yourself such that your ally takes none.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Guard","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"BfH3faE7x5VfS0xX"}
{"name":"Armored Advantage (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\">When you are wearing armor, you gain a +1 insight bonus to your Kinetic Armor Class.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"CWzufxHjOhFM0aDw"}
{"name":"Prepared Shot (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[j60rojbL3unRF31n]{Sharpshoot}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can study a target before you attack. The target must be within line of sight of you and either flat-footed or unaware of your presence. On the first attack you make against that target on your next turn, you gain a +2 bonus to your attack roll. If your attack hits, the target is staggered for 1 round; if you score a critical hit, the target is instead stunned for 1 round. Once you make a prepared shot, you canâ€™t use this ability again against the same target for 24 hours. You canâ€™t make an attack on the same round you study the target, even if an ability would let you attack without spending a standard or full action.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sharpshoot","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"CyLncUPmchglyF1Q"}
{"name":"Armor Storm","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\"></span>The armor storm fighting style focuses on using armor as a weapon by maximizing the damage of armor-based weapons while withstanding enemy fire. You learn to increase the effectiveness of attacks made with your armor and to add equipment normally beyond your armorâ€™s capacity.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[z956k4gQWwypCrqW]{Hammer Fist (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You treat any unarmed attack you make while wearing heavy or powered armor as being made with a battleglove (see page 187) with an item level equal to or lower than your soldier level, and you calculate damage for these attacks as if you had the melee striker gear boost (see page 112). If you have the melee striker gear boost, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls with your unarmed attacks when using this ability. These unarmed attacks donâ€™t benefit from other abilities that apply specifically to unarmed attacks (such as the Improved Unarmed Strike feat).</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[LoEOhgIB1q3FShxo]{Enhanced Tank (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You gain the Powered Armored Proficiency feat and access to improved armor. This might be the result of your own engineering abilities, having earned the trust of contacts that can get you experimental equipment, or a powerful patron giving you gear not available to the general public to help you achieve mutual goals. You can add one more upgrade to your armor than its normal maximum number of upgrade slots. If you add this bonus upgrade to heavy armor, you can select an upgrade normally limited to powered armor. An upgrade placed in this bonus slot costs half the normal credit amount.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[SHanByt8YRPESlNP]{Smash Through (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>While you are wearing heavy armor or powered armor, you gain a +4 bonus to attack rolls to perform a bull rush combat maneuver (see page 246). If you successfully push the target back 10 feet or more, you can also damage the target with an unarmed attack (and can use your hammer fist ability when doing so).</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[0Dxyp6XGrDXYhs6t]{Mobile Army (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You become a master of all weapons associated with your armor. You deal 1d6 additional damage with any attack from a weapon that is part of your armor, including unarmed attacks using the hammer fist ability and weapons that have been attached to your armor as an armor upgrade. The additional damage is of the same type as the weaponâ€™s normal type. Also, while wearing heavy or powered armor, you gain a +2 bonus to your KAC against combat maneuvers.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[7eVNM8KfL0tY2RAM]{On the Bounce (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You learn to control your armor with such ease, you are actually more maneuverable in it than out of it. While wearing heavy armor or powered armor, you can move up to your speed when you make a full attack. You can move before or after all your attacks, but not both. If you have the Shot on the Run feat, you can divide your movement to move both before and after making a full attack as long as all the attacks are ranged attacks. If you have the Spring Attack feat, you can divide your movement to move both before and after making a full attack as long as all the attacks are melee attacks. If you have both feats, your attacks can be any combination of melee and ranged attacks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"DHsDfzkhIOO9ks9m"}
{"name":"Kill Shot (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[WXbhhtFOi9TdKT0y]{Soldier}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can make a single attack against an enemy. If the attack hits and does not kill your enemy, you can expend 1 Resolve Point to force the creature to succeed at a Fortitude save or die. Once you&rsquo;ve used this ability on a creature (regardless of whether or not you forced it to attempt a Fortitude save), that creature is immune to your kill shot for 24 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"20th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"EY4GisYuAtw6v3jl"}
{"name":"Powerful Explosive (Ex; 7th Level)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl03_LabelName\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl18_LabelName\">When you attack with a weapon with the explode special property and a radius of 10 feet or greater, you can increase the radius of the explosion by 5 feet.</span><br></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"7th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"EeJcbJoemrQCjKLx"}
{"name":"Nimble Fusillade (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[FoZjqRj66PMeoSLh]{Hit-and-Run}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">When you make a full attack, you can also either take a guarded step or move up to half your speed. This movement can come before, between, or after your attacks, but it canâ€™t be split up.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Hit-and-Run","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"FbiT8kKJuXdFNrod"}
{"name":"Anchoring Arcana (Su; 7th Level)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a full action, you can make a single attack with a magic weapon against a single foe. If the attack is a ranged attack, the target must be within the first range increment. Even if the attack normally affects an area or multiple targets, it affects only your selected target. If your attack hits, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to force the target to attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 10 + half your soldier level + your key ability score modifier). If the target fails its save, it canâ€™t voluntarily move from its current space for 1d4 rounds. This has no effect on involuntary movement, but it does prevent the creature from teleporting or moving to another plane. Once youâ€™ve struck a foe with this attack, whether it succeeds at or fails its saving throw, it is immune to this ability for 24 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"full","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"7th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"FjgSDpZL8kTTHbzf"}
{"name":"Sharpshoot","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\"></span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">The sharpshoot fighting style enables you to excel at making accurate attacks, usually with ranged weapons at a long distance. You can ignore cover and other impediments to your shots, and your attacks are improved by your intense focus.<br><br></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[PlRvNsetzHgOj12Z]{Sniper's Aim (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you make a ranged attack against a target with cover, reduce the AC bonus from cover by 2. You canâ€™t use sniperâ€™s aim against an enemy with total cover.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[eJQYDoWyep5xHNsM]{Focus Fire (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you make a full attack with a ranged weapon, you can make both attacks with a â€“3 penalty instead of a â€“4 penalty as long as they both target the same creature. If your first attack kills or knocks out the target, you can instead make the second attack against a different creature at a â€“4 penalty. Once you have the soldierâ€™s onslaught class feature (see page 112), you can use this ability with it, making three attacks against the same creature at a â€“5 penalty; if your first or second attack kills or knocks out your target, you can make your remaining attacks against a different creature at a â€“6 penalty.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[dSjHRoAFKE7YlR1n]{Intense Focus (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you make a ranged attack against a target with cover or concealment, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to negate its AC bonus from cover and reduce its concealment by one category (from total concealment to concealment or from concealment to no concealment). This benefit applies to all ranged attacks you make against that target this round. You canâ€™t use intense focus more than once per round, nor can you use it against an enemy with total cover.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[uPV8Qr1d7L1DYxwl]{Focused Damage (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you use focus fire, each attack against the first target deals 2d6 additional damage. Additional creatures you attack after killing or knocking out your first target donâ€™t take this extra damage.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[Pte9RDwhBnmD2yvY]{Prepared Shot (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a standard action, you can study a target before you attack. The target must be within line of sight of you and either flat-footed or unaware of your presence. On the first attack you make against that target on your next turn, you gain a +2 bonus to your attack roll. If your attack hits, the target is staggered for 1 round; if you score a critical hit, the target is instead stunned for 1 round. Once you make a prepared shot, you canâ€™t use this ability again against the same target for 24 hours. You canâ€™t make an attack on the same round you study the target, even if an ability would let you attack without spending a standard or full action.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"GPMYNV8CG9E6TYOV"}
{"name":"Brutal Blast (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl03_LabelName\">You gain a +2 insight bonus to damage rolls with weapons that have the blast special property (such as a scattergun). This extra damage applies only to creatures within 10 feet of you; creatures farther away take the normal amount of damage. This bonus increases by 1 for every 4 soldier levels you have.<br></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"HEtVgmz8NnmWSAbi"}
{"name":"Guard","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\"></span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">The guard fighting style focuses on defense. You become adept at wearing armor, protecting against attacks, and enduring damage and other setbacks from attacks that get through your defenses.<br><br></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[VLRfEIScvZshdDpR]{Armor Training (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You reduce the armor check penalty of armor you wear by 1 (to a minimum of 0) and increase the maximum Dexterity bonus allowed by your armor by 1.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[PRcmmX7d5sCu0B5b]{Guard's Protection (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When an ally adjacent to you is damaged by an attack, you can use your reaction to intercede. You take half the damage, and your ally takes the other half. This has no effect on spells, and any conditions delivered by the attack apply to both of you. In addition, you are now proficient with powered armor.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[Chr5XGfB6E270BM2]{Rapid Recovery (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You can spend Resolve Points to ignore detrimental conditions. As a move action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to suppress one of the following conditions for 10 minutes: exhausted, fatigued, frightened, nauseated, shaken, sickened, or staggered (see pages 276â€“277). After 10 minutes, if the conditionâ€™s duration hasnâ€™t ended, the conditionâ€™s effects return. You can suppress only one condition at a time; if you are both fatigued and shaken, you can avoid the effects of only one of them, and if you are affected by two different instances of the same condition, youâ€™re still affected by the second one.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[KXqB9GFohPcYO4Co]{Kinetic Resistance (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You gain DR 3/â€”. At 17th level, this DR increases to 5/â€”.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[8yDD13N70xumkx2y]{Impenetrable Defense (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a standard action, you can set up a strong defense for yourself and an adjacent ally. Until the start of your next turn, you gain three benefits: your damage reduction increases to DR 10/â€”; you and the chosen ally each gain a +4 bonus to AC; and if you use guardâ€™s protection, you direct all the damage to yourself such that your ally takes none.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"HaBqmvpcChauZtUy"}
{"name":"Debilitating Attack (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">@Item[FkuDc522TWw3WGHE]{Bombard}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">When you hit an enemy with a ranged attack or an attack with a weapon with the blast or explode special property, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to inflict a debilitating effect on that enemy for a number of rounds equal to your Strength bonus. You can choose to make the target deafened, flat-footed, or off-target (see pages 275â€“277), or to reduce its speeds by half (to a minimum of 10 feet). The target can negate this effect with a successful Fortitude save (DC = 10 + half your soldier level + your Strength modifier).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Bombard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"HcX3FAcX17JatBxP"}
{"name":"Opening Volley (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[FoZjqRj66PMeoSLh]{Hit-and-Run}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You gain Opening Volley as a bonus feat. If you already have this feat, choose a bonus combat feat instead. At 9th level, you can use Opening Volley on both your first and second turns in combat.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Hit-and-Run","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"K2E4K0qCYAPPZrkr"}
{"name":"Enhanced Tank (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[ZST4GXqgA9b9CzNU]{Armor Storm}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You gain the Powered Armored Proficiency feat and access to improved armor. This might be the result of your own engineering abilities, having earned the trust of contacts that can get you experimental equipment, or a powerful patron giving you gear not available to the general public to help you achieve mutual goals. You can add one more upgrade to your armor than its normal maximum number of upgrade slots. If you add this bonus upgrade to heavy armor, you can select an upgrade normally limited to powered armor. An upgrade placed in this bonus slot costs half the normal credit amount.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Armor Storm","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"KQKR1G1cvKcMbsmq"}
{"name":"Arcane Assailant","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\">The arcane assailant fighting style supplements its combat effectiveness with magic powers, drawing on traditions of warrior-wizards dating back to well before the Gap. This allows you to use magic runes to augment your weapons and call on legendary powers, giving you access to arcane options even when you donâ€™t have a magic weapon in your possession.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[EKekQpaRatV224gN]{Rune of the Eldritch Knight (Su; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You can imbue a weapon with a magic sigil, the rune of the eldritch knight, allowing the weapon to act as a magic weapon for the purposes of bypassing DR and affecting incorporeal creatures. This takes 10 minutes, and you can imbue only a single weapon at a time. If you imbue a new weapon with the rune of the eldritch knight, any previously imbued weapon loses this benefit. When calculating the Hit Points and hardness of a weapon imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight, treat its item level as 5 higher.<br></span></p>\n<h2>@Item[M6Cw0SxKHXUj4DXW]{Secret of the Magi (Su; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you imbue a weapon with the rune of the eldritch knight, in addition to its normal benefits, the rune grants the weapon one of the following weapon fusions of your choice: <em>ethereal</em>, <em>flaming</em>, <em>frost</em>, <em>merciful</em>, or <em>shock</em>. The weapon canâ€™t gain a fusion it already has, and this bonus fusion doesnâ€™t count toward the maximum total level of fusions the weapon can have at once. The bonus fusion ends when the weapon ceases to be imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight. For more information on fusions, see page 191.</p>\n<h2>@Item[CFAqkP6glhcZZsmw]{Power of Legend (Su; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You can call on the link between you and the legendary heroes who wielded powerful magic weapons eons ago to overcome adversity. As a move action when wielding a magic weapon or a weapon imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to end one of the following conditions affecting you: bleeding, burning, confused, exhausted, fatigued, flat-footed, off-target, shaken, or sickened. Alternatively, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to change the cowering condition to the frightened condition or change the frightened condition to the shaken condition. In this case, the new condition lasts for the same duration the original condition would have and canâ€™t be further affected by this ability.</p>\n<h2>@Item[Yki2hC9orNakRiSp]{Secret of the Archmagi (Su; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You can imbue two weapons with the rune of the eldritch knight. If you attempt to imbue a third weapon, the weapon infused first loses its rune and all benefits. In addition to the normal benefits, the runes grant the weapons one or more of the following weapon fusions (see page 191) of your choice: <em>bane</em>, <em>corrosive</em>, <em>ethereal</em>, <em>flaming</em>, <em>frost</em>, <em>holy</em>, <em>merciful</em>, <em>shock</em>, <em>thundering</em>, or <em>unholy</em>. You can grant no more than 10 total levelsâ€™ worth of fusions between the two weapons, and the bane fusion counts as a 10th-level fusion for this purpose.</p>\n<h2>@Item[rZGFDN7CBW6nlFxH]{Arcane Attack (Su; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a standard action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to use a weapon imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight to make an attack that strikes true. This attack ignores all cover and concealment, including total concealment (though you must at least be aware of a creatureâ€™s presence to target it with this attack). If the attack is a ranged attack, the target must be within the first range increment. The attack only affects your selected target, even if it normally affects an area or multiple targets. You still must make a normal attack roll, and if your attack misses, it has no effect.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"Mf41DS0UZdPMws2d"}
{"name":"Soldier's Onslaught (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[WXbhhtFOi9TdKT0y]{Soldier}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">When you make a full attack, you can make up to three attacks instead of two attacks. You take a &ndash;6 penalty to these attacks instead of a &ndash;4 penalty.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"11th Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"PQlf8Wrhi0wRkH4L"}
{"name":"Rapid Response (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-entity=\"Item\" data-id=\"cR8wnyEBfjeelFdA\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Blitz</a></p>\n        <p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You gain a +4 bonus to initiative checks and increase your land speed by 10 feet.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Blitz","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"PcyUJKIDICsnvmAl"}
{"name":"Blitz","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\"></span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">The blitz fighting style is all about using speed and aggression to get into the thick of melee. You increase your speed and responsiveness, gain abilities that make you better at melee combat than your enemies, and keep on fighting even when surrounded by foes.<br><br></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[B5swZs7Rnbur7NJn]{Rapid Response (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You gain a +4 bonus to initiative checks and increase your land speed by 10 feet.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[GLWTmtMnyaVZLbkg]{Charge Attack (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a standard action, you can make a charge without the charge penalties (see page 248), and you can substitute a bull rush for the melee attack at the end of the charge. When you gain the soldierâ€™s onslaught class feature, you can make two attacks instead of one at the end of your charge, both with a â€“4 penalty.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[oFZ2RA22yW9qKYUi]{Keep Fighting (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a move action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to regain Stamina Points equal to 2d6 + your soldier level. You canâ€™t use this ability again until after you regain Stamina Points from a 10-minute rest. The number of Stamina Points you regain increases by 1d6 at 10th level, 15th level, and 20th level.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[OWNe42EVhy1aQGG3]{Perfect Opportunity (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you hit a creature with an attack of opportunity, that creature canâ€™t move out of the squares you threaten until the start of its next turn. In addition, when an enemy takes a guarded step (see page 247) out of a square you threaten, you can make an attack of opportunity against it with a â€“2 penalty to the attack roll. If the target provoked an attack of opportunity by moving, hitting with your attack of opportunity ends the targetâ€™s movement immediately, preventing it from carrying out the rest of its movement.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[O3Y06678ok0mkHcf]{Against the Odds (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You gain a bonus to melee damage rolls equal to double the number of enemies within 10 feet of you. Enemies who donâ€™t constitute a significant threat (those with a CR equal to your level â€“ 4 or less, or as determined by the GM) donâ€™t count when calculating this bonus.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"QScp8zO3dzGwWXDn"}
{"name":"Combat Feat","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[WXbhhtFOi9TdKT0y]{Soldier}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">At 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a bonus feat in addition to those gained from normal advancement. These bonus feats must be selected from those listed as combat feats.<br><br>Whenever you gain a new bonus feat, you can also choose to replace one of the bonus feats you have already learned with a different bonus feat. The feat you replace canâ€™t be one that was used as a prerequisite for another feat or other ability. You can change only one feat at any given level, and you must choose whether or not to swap the feat at the time you gain the new bonus feat.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"QX7RdpqkPuiB1aFp"}
{"name":"Keep Fighting (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-entity=\"Item\" data-id=\"cR8wnyEBfjeelFdA\"> Blitz</a></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a move action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to regain Stamina Points equal to 2d6 + your soldier level. You canâ€™t use this ability again until after you regain Stamina Points from a 10-minute rest. The number of Stamina Points you regain increases by 1d6 at 10th level, 15th level, and 20th level.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Blitz","type":"","activation":{"type":"move","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"QmsOHHiE6NQewQK3"}
{"name":"Fighting Style","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[WXbhhtFOi9TdKT0y]{Soldier}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">You have a preferred fighting style that represents the type of soldier you are. Each fighting style is composed of various style techniques that you learn as you gain experience. You must pick one fighting style upon taking your first soldier level, and once made, this choice cannot be changed. Descriptions of the fighting styles you can choose from appear on pages 112â€“115.&nbsp;<em>(Or Below)</em></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[33fxlqpShtqndjry]{Arcane Assailant}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\">The arcane assailant fighting style supplements its combat effectiveness with magic powers, drawing on traditions of warrior-wizards dating back to well before the Gap. This allows you to use magic runes to augment your weapons and call on legendary powers, giving you access to arcane options even when you donâ€™t have a magic weapon in your possession.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[ZST4GXqgA9b9CzNU]{Armor Storm}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl02_LabelName\">The armor storm fighting style focuses on using armor as a weapon by maximizing the damage of armor-based weapons while withstanding enemy fire. You learn to increase the effectiveness of attacks made with your armor and to add equipment normally beyond your armorâ€™s capacity.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[cR8wnyEBfjeelFdA]{Blitz}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl04_LabelName\">The blitz fighting style is all about using speed and aggression to get into the thick of melee. You increase your speed and responsiveness, gain abilities that make you better at melee combat than your enemies, and keep on fighting even when surrounded by foes.<br></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[FkuDc522TWw3WGHE]{Bombard}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl05_LabelName\">The bombard fighting style emphasizes attacking multiple targets, often using grenades, and leverages substantial physical strength to control large weapons with significant recoil. At higher levels, you can use launchers, missiles, and other heavy weapons.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[zD0XifvCmxfSzn1Y]{Guard}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl08_LabelName\">The guard fighting style focuses on defense. You become adept at wearing armor, protecting against attacks, and enduring damage and other setbacks from attacks that get through your defenses.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[FoZjqRj66PMeoSLh]{Hit-and-Run}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl09_LabelName\">The hit-and-run fighting style focuses on tactical movement as you move in and out of combat. You use ranged weapons but fight close up, and you can even mix ranged and melee attacks. Your abilities allow you to move even when you make full attacks and to avoid getting locked down by your enemies.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>@Item[j60rojbL3unRF31n]{Sharpshoot}</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl13_LabelName\">The sharpshoot fighting style enables you to excel at making accurate attacks, usually with ranged weapons at a long distance. You can ignore cover and other impediments to your shots, and your attacks are improved by your intense focus.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"SQnVmqO8rt03KyNO"}
{"name":"Focused Damage (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[j60rojbL3unRF31n]{Sharpshoot}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">When you use focus fire, each attack against the first target deals 2d6 additional damage. Additional creatures you attack after killing or knocking out your first target donâ€™t take this extra damage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sharpshoot","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"V8VwPDCgLdPx9FGa"}
{"name":"Harrying Shot (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[FoZjqRj66PMeoSLh]{Hit-and-Run}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a full action, you can make one attack and give the benefit of harrying fire (see page 247) against any creature you hit with that attack. If you use a blast weapon or automatic weapon, the benefit applies against all targets hit. You can also take your nimble fusillade movement before or after this attack.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Hit-and-Run","type":"","activation":{"type":"full","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"WC2BUQKLcqWUSW0R"}
{"name":"Smash Through (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[ZST4GXqgA9b9CzNU]{Armor Storm}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">While you are wearing heavy armor or powered armor, you gain a +4 bonus to attack rolls to perform a bull rush combat maneuver (see page 246). If you successfully push the target back 10 feet or more, you can also damage the target with an unarmed attack (and can use your hammer fist ability when doing so).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Armor Storm","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"YEa1PF7Im0nZ75ez"}
{"name":"Duck and Weave (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[FoZjqRj66PMeoSLh]{Hit-and-Run}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">When you move or make a ranged attack, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to avoid provoking attacks of opportunity from that movement or ranged attack.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Hit-and-Run","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"YU0p5j9bjcS1UEKH"}
{"name":"Melee Striker (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl03_LabelName\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl15_LabelName\">Add an additional bonus equal to half your Strength bonus to damage rolls with melee weapons.</span><br></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"Zkz5KTx4hCFsgqVp"}
{"name":"Rune of the Eldritch Knight (Su; 1st, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[33fxlqpShtqndjry]{Arcane Assailant}</p>\n<p>You can imbue a weapon with a magic sigil, the rune of the eldritch knight, allowing the weapon to act as a magic weapon for the purposes of bypassing DR and affecting incorporeal creatures. This takes 10 minutes, and you can imbue only a single weapon at a time. If you imbue a new weapon with the rune of the eldritch knight, any previously imbued weapon loses this benefit. When calculating the Hit Points and hardness of a weapon imbued with the rune of the eldritch knight, treat its item level as 5 higher.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Arcane Assailant","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"bkrXgIQZdxXonfR5"}
{"name":"Hammer Fist (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[ZST4GXqgA9b9CzNU]{Armor Storm}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You treat any unarmed attack you make while wearing heavy or powered armor as being made with a battleglove (see page 187) with an item level equal to or lower than your soldier level, and you calculate damage for these attacks as if you had the melee striker gear boost (see page 112). If you have the melee striker gear boost, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls with your unarmed attacks when using this ability. These unarmed attacks donâ€™t benefit from other abilities that apply specifically to unarmed attacks (such as the Improved Unarmed Strike feat).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Armor Storm","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"c7mG4AQZeLh55j1q"}
{"name":"Laser Accuracy (Ex)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[wFTC0sGqdpnZUib4]{Gear Boost}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl03_LabelName\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl13_LabelName\">You gain a +1 insight bonus to attack rolls with weapons in the laser category.</span><br /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Gear Boost","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"djQ5C4PAPlGSF0nb"}
{"name":"Secret of the Archmagi (Su; 4th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[33fxlqpShtqndjry]{Arcane Assailant}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You can imbue two weapons with the rune of the eldritch knight. If you attempt to imbue a third weapon, the weapon infused first loses its rune and all benefits. In addition to the normal benefits, the runes grant the weapons one or more of the following weapon fusions (see page 191) of your choice: <em>bane</em>, <em>corrosive</em>, <em>ethereal</em>, <em>flaming</em>, <em>frost</em>, <em>holy</em>, <em>merciful</em>, <em>shock</em>, <em>thundering</em>, or <em>unholy</em>. You can grant no more than 10 total levels&rsquo; worth of fusions between the two weapons, and the bane fusion counts as a 10th-level fusion for this purpose.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Arcane Assailant","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"4th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"dpVd4KqB0AlvhaeC"}
{"_id":"dsjQCkeB8Bs8Hr0z","name":"Against the Odds (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-entity=\"Item\" data-id=\"cR8wnyEBfjeelFdA\"> Blitz</a></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You gain a bonus to melee damage rolls equal to double the number of enemies within 10 feet of you. Enemies who donâ€™t constitute a significant threat (those with a CR equal to your level â€“ 4 or less, or as determined by the GM) donâ€™t count when calculating this bonus.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Blitz","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"5th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"name":"Rapid Recovery (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[zD0XifvCmxfSzn1Y]{Guard}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You can spend Resolve Points to ignore detrimental conditions. As a move action, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to suppress one of the following conditions for 10 minutes: exhausted, fatigued, frightened, nauseated, shaken, sickened, or staggered (see pages 276â€“277). After 10 minutes, if the conditionâ€™s duration hasnâ€™t ended, the conditionâ€™s effects return. You can suppress only one condition at a time; if you are both fatigued and shaken, you can avoid the effects of only one of them, and if you are affected by two different instances of the same condition, youâ€™re still affected by the second one.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Guard","type":"","activation":{"type":"move","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"ekuLfTPSrRv0psDs"}
{"name":"Charge Attack (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;<a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-entity=\"Item\" data-id=\"cR8wnyEBfjeelFdA\"> Blitz</a></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">As a standard action, you can make a charge without the charge penalties (see page 248), and you can substitute a bull rush for the melee attack at the end of the charge. When you gain the soldierâ€™s onslaught class feature, you can make two attacks instead of one at the end of your charge, both with a â€“4 penalty.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Blitz","type":"","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"fajBV1kJDNbUEtoB"}
{"name":"Guard's Protection (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[zD0XifvCmxfSzn1Y]{Guard}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">When an ally adjacent to you is damaged by an attack, you can use your reaction to intercede. You take half the damage, and your ally takes the other half. This has no effect on spells, and any conditions delivered by the attack apply to both of you. In addition, you are now proficient with powered armor.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Guard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"2nd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"gP14CVgDgeLffANE"}
{"name":"Bombard","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\"></span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">The bombard fighting style emphasizes attacking multiple targets, often using grenades, and leverages substantial physical strength to control large weapons with significant recoil. At higher levels, you can use launchers, missiles, and other heavy weapons.<br><br></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[0ij00QIm2bfnxJLG]{Grenade Expert (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You increase the range increment of your thrown grenades by 5 Ã— your Strength bonus. In addition, youâ€™re able to salvage enough materials to create a grenade without paying for it. Creating a grenade takes 10 minutes. You can create any grenade whose item level is less than or equal to your soldier level, but this grenade is unstable and only you can use it effectively. If anyone else tries to use the grenade, it is a dud. You can have only one grenade created by this ability at one time (if you create a new grenade using this ability, the old grenade no longer works).</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[ezO0OWogqlFdQC7w]{Heavy Fire (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You can use your physical power to steady your weapon and make your attacks more dangerous. As a full action, you can make a single ranged attack that deals additional damage equal to your Strength bonus to all targets. You can use this ability in conjunction with the automatic, explode, or unwieldy special property (see pages 180â€“182).</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[XfBy2mvDU4kougdq]{Debilitating Attack (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you hit an enemy with a ranged attack or an attack with a weapon with the blast or explode special property, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to inflict a debilitating effect on that enemy for a number of rounds equal to your Strength bonus. You can choose to make the target deafened, flat-footed, or off-target (see pages 275â€“277), or to reduce its speeds by half (to a minimum of 10 feet). The target can negate this effect with a successful Fortitude save (DC = 10 + half your soldier level + your Strength modifier).</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[TTH8JsxILLGZpmpj]{Explosives Acumen (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You increase the DC to avoid attacks you make using weapons with the explode special property by 1. You reduce the amount of any damage you take from any weapon with the explode special property by an amount equal to your Strength bonus.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[mvcBpO0c1UjYkxl1]{Impactful Attack (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a full action, you can make a ranged attack that knocks enemies back. Targets you hit are knocked back 5 feet from you. If you use a weapon with the explode special property, all targets that fail their saving throws are instead knocked back 5 feet from the center of the explosion. An enemy that you critically hit or that rolls a natural 1 on its saving throw is also knocked prone. You canâ€™t make an impactful attack with an automatic weapon, but you can use this ability with a weapon that has the blast special property.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"jBy7jiVbxOj7Kmbi"}
{"name":"Intense Focus (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[j60rojbL3unRF31n]{Sharpshoot}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">When you make a ranged attack against a target with cover or concealment, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to negate its AC bonus from cover and reduce its concealment by one category (from total concealment to concealment or from concealment to no concealment). This benefit applies to all ranged attacks you make against that target this round. You canâ€™t use intense focus more than once per round, nor can you use it against an enemy with total cover.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sharpshoot","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"jFfmvHQSilTEl3ox"}
{"name":"Kinetic Resistance (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[zD0XifvCmxfSzn1Y]{Guard}</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">You gain DR 3/â€”. At 17th level, this DR increases to 5/â€”.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Guard","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":null,"shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":null,"additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":null,"per":""},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"4th Bonus","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"l6dpAaYJI6nqGakq"}
{"name":"Hit-and-Run","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>&gt;@Item[Kt54ML6r6xAY0Hba]{Fighting Style}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl01_LabelName\"></span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTalentsAll_ctl00_LabelName\">The hit-and-run fighting style focuses on tactical movement as you move in and out of combat. You use ranged weapons but fight close up, and you can even mix ranged and melee attacks. Your abilities allow you to move even when you make full attacks and to avoid getting locked down by your enemies.<br><br></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[AMmOKEWzPGfWOgs4]{Opening Volley (Ex; 1st, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>You gain Opening Volley as a bonus feat. If you already have this feat, choose a bonus combat feat instead. At 9th level, you can use Opening Volley on both your first and second turns in combat.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[lVUCebWWOwFLtEdL]{Nimble Fusillade (Ex; 2nd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you make a full attack, you can also either take a guarded step or move up to half your speed. This movement can come before, between, or after your attacks, but it canâ€™t be split up.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[aOHlRteyBF2uObtF]{Duck and Weave (Ex; 3rd, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>When you move or make a ranged attack, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to avoid provoking attacks of opportunity from that movement or ranged attack.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[FVgta1LAnseCP3vy]{Elusive Target (Ex; 4th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>On any turn in which you move, you gain a +1 insight bonus to your AC until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<h2 class=\"title\">@Item[eZ3ZYYHxggpyQZCI]{Harrying Shot (Ex; 5th, Fighting Style)}</h2>\n<p>As a full action, you can make one attack and give the benefit of harrying fire (see page 247) against any creature you hit with that attack. If you use a blast weapon or automatic weapon, the benefit applies against all targets hit. You can also take your nimble fusillade movement before or after this attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Fighting Style","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"1st level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"practice-starfinder","system":"sfrpg","coreVersion":"0.6.5","systemVersion":"0.3.3"}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"mVRVFg1bUepywZ0n"}
{"name":"Gear Boost","permission":{"default":0,"hg1bBCAUsIDPKim6":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">&gt;@Item[WXbhhtFOi9TdKT0y]{Soldier}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListClasses_ctl00_LabelName\">At 3rd level and every 4 levels thereafter, you learn a trick called a gear boost that make you better with a particular type of weapon or armor. Choose from the gear boosts listed below. Some gear boosts require you to reach a certain soldier level to select them; this level is indicated in parentheses after the boostâ€™s name.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Item[wf7s0APxkXXfElpT]{Anchoring Arcana (Su; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Item[v4HHvGkb4kmZ0XEL]{Armored Advantage (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Item[rbGTGyfZerNU7eRI]{Brutal Blast (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Item[dsMBszemiygcKXAe]{Bullet Barrage (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Item[n3CapyEdO6GO0fC8]{Electric Arc (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Item[CmWcFwVnP7bjIsXC]{Flash Freeze (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Item[mensJxPQRInQkmJQ]{Heavy Onslaught (Ex; 11th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Item[8CPBQDOk76JPjH7F]{Laser Accuracy (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Item[neLxjVshsK2SSkJA]{Melee Striker (Ex)}</p>\n<p>@Item[hU6gtmt64IxddU4O]{Plasma Immolation (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Item[nl3noEbVA1E8NjXl]{Powerful Explosive (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>\n<p>@Item[5mOIWLb0Aa5VmFR6]{Sonic Resonance (Ex; 7th Level)}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Soldier","type":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"type":""},"area":{"value":null,"units":"","shape":"","effect":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","additional":"","per":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"parts":[],"effect":""},"damage":{"parts":[]},"formula":"","save":{"type":"","dc":null,"descriptor":""},"descriptors":[],"modifiers":[],"requirements":"3rd Level","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"abilityMods":